verbose_text: Combined analysis of the expression patterns of CsPDATs and TAG accumulation trends in camelina seedlings under four different types of stresses indicated that CsPDAT1-A, CsPDAT2-A, CsPDAT2-B and CsPDAT1-C may be the key contributors for TAG biosynthesis in response to cold, drought, salt and osmotic stresses, respectively.
evidence: CsPDAT1-C may be the key contributors for TAG biosynthesis
